#
# ThreadSanitizer race suppressions for eternaltermlib's -DET_SANITIZE=thread
# build (Task 8). Point TSan at this file via:
#   TSAN_OPTIONS="suppressions=/work/.tsan-suppressions"
# (the test CMake wires this automatically via the ET_TSAN_SUPPRESSIONS env on
# each add_test).
#
# SCOPE RULE: every entry below is a race whose BOTH racing accesses live
# entirely inside VENDORED upstream Eternal Terminal (extern/eternalterminal/),
# which this repo may not modify (see CLAUDE.md "do NOT modify extern/"). No
# first-party file (src/session.cpp, src/transport.cpp) is suppressed — a race
# reported *there* is ours and must be fixed, not muted. Verified: the only
# first-party race TSan found (the et_close heap-use-after-free on the
# CloseIsIdempotent path) was FIXED in src/session.cpp (external live-handle
# registry), not suppressed.
#
# ROOT CAUSE (all four below are the same upstream defect): ET's
# Connection::socketFd is written under connectionMutex by closeSocket() /
# closeSocketAndMaybeReconnect() / recover(), but read WITHOUT the mutex by the
# inline Connection::getSocketFd() (Connection.hpp:50) and BackedWriter's
# sequence-number path. Our transport thread reads the fd each loop iteration
# (the documented ET usage, mirroring upstream TerminalClient) while the close
# path / ET's own reconnect thread mutate it. The read is benign in practice
# (an int load that at worst yields a momentarily-stale fd, re-checked next
# 10ms select tick), but it is a genuine unsynchronized access in upstream code
# we cannot patch here. Reported upstream-relevant; suppressed to keep OUR
# threading model's TSan signal clean.

# getSocketFd(): unsynchronized read of Connection::socketFd (Connection.hpp:50).
race:et::Connection::getSocketFd

# closeSocket(): writes socketFd under the lock, racing the unlocked read above.
race:et::Connection::closeSocket

# recover()/reconnect path: ET's own reconnect thread rewrites writer/fd state
# racing the transport thread's writePacket (Connection.cpp / BackedWriter.cpp).
race:et::Connection::recover
race:et::BackedWriter::write
